how nice to read the posts in here...moved me deeply...we all may have had a terror in our lives related to VN...soldiers went and came home, and they were called &quot;hereo's&quot;  by some and called &quot;baby killers&quot; by others.  some didn't go, and were called &quot;hero's&quot; by some and &quot;cowards&quot; by others...which ever you were, you will were that sign forever.<br><br>
i admit, i didn't think it would take me this long to read about, to try and understand the TRUTH about what the US gov didn't want anyone to know about our envolvement in VN, laos, and cambodia. it's almost a full time job to read, to know/understand the depth of the war.<br><br>
the VN experience and the draft/slavery cost me 11  years of my life, and a trauma that will stay with me to my grave.<br><br>
i will fight for the truth to the end, no matter which way it turns, or who/what gets in the way.<br><br>
peace V<br><br>
